Good.
You remembered.

16
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:22,392
Get everyone to safety.

17
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:24,853
But not too far.
Understand? Go.

18
00:02:35,321 --> 00:02:38,366
- You're delaying the inevitable.
- You could have killed Doyle.

19
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:40,326
- You didn't.
- I'll get to him.

20
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:43,079
I'm much more interested in you.

21
00:02:44,247 --> 00:02:47,500
Memories were fuzzy,
like an orange left out too long,

22
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:49,377
but I could still find my way back.

23
00:02:50,753 --> 00:02:52,297
- Thank you.
- My pleasure.

24
00:02:54,173 --> 00:02:56,634
Been a while since my body
and mind were together.

25
00:02:58,136 --> 00:02:59,554
Be a crisis for a lesser man

26
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:02,181
having your soul ripped out of you,
but not for me.

27
00:03:02,807 --> 00:03:04,017
I returned...

28
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:07,103
with one simple,

29
00:03:07,937 --> 00:03:10,148
- singular thought.
- I know. Don't tell me.

30
00:03:10,481 --> 00:03:11,482
Fun.

31
00:03:12,442 --> 00:03:13,526
Feast.

32
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:20,909
Love what you've done
with the place.

33
00:03:21,951 --> 00:03:24,245
Brought a lot more people in here.

34
00:03:25,163 --> 00:03:27,165
Gonna make me a lot more powerful.

35
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:29,125
No, it makes me more powerful.

36
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,045
I got big plans for you.

37
00:03:33,296 --> 00:03:34,964
Kill me now, you'll never know.

38
00:03:35,131 --> 00:03:37,634
Everybody has big plans for me.

39
00:03:38,384 --> 00:03:40,345
I think that's all people have.

40
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:29,727
Subtitles: Rebel
www.sous-titres.eu

41
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:54,711
You all right?

42
00:04:55,378 --> 00:04:59,340
I... wasn't expecting to see you.

43
00:05:01,509 --> 00:05:03,094
I thought I'd give you a lift.

44
00:05:07,265 --> 00:05:08,599
You don't want a ride?

45
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:16,733
I'd prefer if you didn't come.

46
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:19,652
You lied to me.

47
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:22,405
Once again.

48
00:05:23,448 --> 00:05:25,533
About Nathan's death,
about what you did.

49
00:05:27,743 --> 00:05:28,745
God.

50
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:32,123
It was Sylar.

51
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:35,626
Did you...

52
00:05:35,793 --> 00:05:38,588
forget that it was Sylar?

53
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:40,632
Did you forget what he did to me?

54
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,301
He attacked me.

55
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,970
He cut open my head.

56
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:48,890
He killed my father.

57
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:50,224
And you,

58
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:54,771
you dressed him up in Nathan's face,
and I hugged him.

59
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:58,149
And I felt love for him.

60
00:05:58,733 --> 00:05:59,984
We did the wrong thing

61
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,653
for the right reason.

62
00:06:03,071 --> 00:06:04,780
We found a way to contain Sylar

63
00:06:04,947 --> 00:06:07,158
and to keep Nathan alive
at the same time.

64
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:12,121
- It didn't work. We shouldn't have.
- You did.

65
00:06:13,247 --> 00:06:16,334
And I need time to grieve
without being reminded why.

66
00:06:41,109 --> 00:06:43,569
I keep looking up too,
hoping to see him.

67
00:06:45,863 --> 00:06:49,075
We never have been
very good with death, have we?

68
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:50,910
Or it's complications.

69
00:06:52,328 --> 00:06:55,164
Can't have been easy for you,
covering this all up with Noah.

70
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:58,501
- How are you?
- Okay.

71
00:06:58,668 --> 00:06:59,585
I'm okay.

72
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:02,588
- Nathan was a better liar.
- He got that from you.

73
00:07:05,716 --> 00:07:07,635
I'm sorry.
You don't deserve that.

74
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:10,221
Sure I do.
I deserve every ounce of your wrath.

75
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:11,597
No, you don't.

76
00:07:12,014 --> 00:07:14,392
Just want to put my fist
through a wall right now.

77
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:16,644
No, you want to put a fist
through Sylar.

78
00:07:19,438 --> 00:07:21,232
- What do you want?
- Don't do it.

79
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:23,067
Nathan was right.

80
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:27,530
You need to fight the good fight.
Revenge will only get you killed.

81
00:07:28,531 --> 00:07:30,450
And I cannot bear to lose you too.

82
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:37,165
Claire's here.

83
00:07:43,504 --> 00:07:45,631
You want to help me in the kitchen?

84
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:48,176
- You trying to escape?
- As quickly as possible.

85
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,596
Why don't you take a break?

86
00:07:53,514 --> 00:07:54,515
Thanks.

87
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:02,190
Where's your dad?
Didn't see him out there.

88
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:06,611
I asked him not to come.

89
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:10,114
- You're pissed.
- You're not?

90
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:11,908
Oh, I am.

91
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:16,704
Good, 'cause you're the only person
who's on the same page as me.

92
00:08:18,748 --> 00:08:21,000
- That's a hell of a lie.
- Trying to protect us.

93
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,920
Yeah. That's fine.
I get that...

94
00:08:25,296 --> 00:08:28,174
Did they really think
that they were gonna get away with it?

95
00:08:29,216 --> 00:08:31,928
Forever? That we would
just never find out?

96
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:33,262
Damn it!

97
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:36,724
It's not healing.

98
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:42,355
I have the Haitian's power.
I'll... sorry, I'll turn it off.

99
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:43,940
No, don't, don't.

100
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:47,485
Let me find you a band-aid.

101
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:53,240
A band-aid.
I have not used a band-aid in forever.

102
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:56,327
It's nice to feel pain.

103
00:08:56,994 --> 00:08:58,120
Feel normal.

104
00:08:59,288 --> 00:09:00,831
We're anything but...

105
00:09:01,165 --> 00:09:02,125
Normal.

106
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:07,463
Mourning Nathan
could not be more ordinary.

107
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:11,884
That's what we're here to do.

108
00:09:12,468 --> 00:09:14,553
To cut lemons and limes

109
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:17,306
and remember that...

110
00:09:19,266 --> 00:09:20,184
stupid jerk.

111
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:24,981
I can't believe he's gone.

112
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:33,239
I hope he can find heaven,
because he was a terrible navigator.

113
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:35,908
I mean, for a guy who could fly.

114
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:40,871
Why are you laughing?
What's so funny?

115
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:45,126
He gave me endless grief
for dating a guy who could fly.

116
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:49,672
He said I had daddy issues,
which... I do.

117
00:09:51,507 --> 00:09:54,009
Whatever happened to that kid?
What was his name?

118
00:09:54,176 --> 00:09:55,094
West.

119
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,555
He goes to NYU.
We're Facebook friends.

120
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,059
It's nice telling stories.

121
00:10:02,393 --> 00:10:04,145
Makes it a little easier.

122
00:10:05,604 --> 00:10:07,982
What about about you?
You must have a million of 'em.

123
00:10:13,487 --> 00:10:15,907
I'm gonna take these out there.

124
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:25,684
Won't get fooled again.

